
// This Hyperlambda code checks if the value of the [flag] node is true. If it is, it sets the value of the [result] node to "Yes". The [if] slot uses a shorthand version where the condition is directly specified as an expression, and the action to perform is nested within the [if] node itself.
if:x:@.flag
   set-value:x:@.result
      .:Yes
